3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on secure communication and eavesdropping, which are core topics in cryptography and security. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a power allocation scheme for a wireless-powered system, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): Although not directly related to multimedia, the paper involves signal processing and transmission, which are relevant topics in multimedia.
